**1. Executive Summary**

Circular Fertiliser Industries (CFI) is a palm oil mill waste
bioconversion operation located in Bogor, West Java, Indonesia. The host
mill processes 60 tonnes per hour (TPH) of fresh fruit bunches (FFB).
CFI captures three mill waste streams --- Empty Fruit Bunches (EFB), Oil
Palm Decanter Cake (OPDC), and POME sludge --- and transforms them
through a six-stage biological pipeline (S0→S6) into Black Soldier Fly
(BSF)-derived products and biofertiliser frass.

+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+
| **60 TPH FFB**  | **\~720 t/day   | **\~110 t/day   | **\~30 t/day    |
|                 | WW**            | WW**            | WW**            |
| Mill Capacity   |                 |                 |                 |
|                 | EFB Daily       | OPDC Daily      | POME Sludge     |
+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+

+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+
| **\~213,827 t** | **\             | **52--60% CP**  | **\~\$12.50/t   |
|                 | $4.3--6.4M/yr** |                 | FW**            |
| CO₂e Avoided    |                 | BSF Meal Grade  |                 |
| (annual)        | Carbon Revenue  |                 | Frass NPK Value |
+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+-----------------+

The primary customer is the plantation estate operation itself (Sinar
Mas, Wilmar, Astra Agro or equivalent), not smallholder farmers. CFI
supplies biofertiliser back to the estate at a displacement value versus
synthetic NPK.

This brief specifies the complete React dashboard (CFI_FULL_BUILD) to be
built in Lovable, connected to a Supabase backend, covering all pipeline
stages, product valuation, carbon credits, administration, and the
orchestration layer.

