**3. Pipeline Architecture: S0 → S6**

The pipeline consists of seven distinct stages. Each stage has a
dedicated tab in the React dashboard. All stages share a persistent
Nutrient Ledger panel showing N, P, K, Ca, Mg, and OM in both % DM and
kg/day with synthetic fertiliser replacement value.

  ----------- ---------------- ---------------- -------------------- -----------------
  **Stage**   **Name**         **Inputs**       **Outputs**          **Key Gates**

  **S0**      Feedstock Inputs FFB mill         EFB / OPDC / POME    User-adjustable
                               throughput; %    mass balance         capture %
                               capture                               

  **S1**      Pre-Processing   Raw EFB, OPDC,   2mm milled EFB;      EFB: 2mm D90;
                               POME sludge      dewatered OPDC;      OPDC ≥40% MC
                                                decanted sludge      

  **S2**      Chemical         Milled EFB +     30--35% lignin       pH ≤8.0 gate
              Treatment        OPDC; PKSA       reduction; pH        before S3/S4
                                                6.5--8.0 after       
                                                neutralisation       

  **S3**      Biological       pH-neutralised   Biology-ready        5-day hard
              Treatment        substrate;       substrate; 5-day     minimum; Temp
                               microbes         minimum dwell        ≤30°C before BSF

  **S4**      BSF Rearing      Biology-ready    Prepupae (biomass);  pH ≤8.0 Wave-1
                               substrate; BSF   partially-digested   trigger; Temp
                               larvae           frass                \<50°C Wave-2

  **S5**      Product          BSF prepupae +   Insect meal; BSF     Defatting;
              Extraction       frass            oil; chitin; wet     drying;
                                                frass                certification

  **S6**      Frass            Wet frass from   Granulated / bagged  Heavy metal
              Biofertiliser    S4               biofertiliser        screen; NPK label
                                                                     compliance

  **CC**      Carbon Credits   Diverted waste   CO₂e avoided; VCU    FOD + COD IPCC
                               streams          issuance             methods
  ----------- ---------------- ---------------- -------------------- -----------------

