**6. S3 --- Biological Library (43 Organisms)**

The biological library contains 43 organisms across 15 categories. Each
organism has a BSF safety flag (safe / conditional / blocked). The
conflict engine prevents incompatible combinations. BSF is the primary
commercial organism; all others are substrate preparation or enhancement
agents.

**6.1 BSF Inoculation Gates --- HARD CONSTRAINTS**

  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------
  **Gate**                **Condition**           **Type**

  Biological minimum      **5 days dwell before   **HARD GATE ---
                          BSF introduction**      non-negotiable**

  Temperature gate (BSF   **Substrate temperature **HARD GATE**
  entry)                  ≤ 30°C**                

  Wave 1 inoculation      **pH sensor reading ≤   **pH sensor --- NOT
  trigger                 8.0**                   temperature**

  Wave 2 gate             **Temperature \< 50°C** Protects N-fixing
                                                  bacteria

  Bt (Provibio ICBB 6095) **S3 composting phase   **⚠ CONDITIONAL ---
                          ONLY before BSF;        amber warning
                          confirm titre \< 10⁴    required**
                          CFU/g before S4         
                          loading**               
  ----------------------- ----------------------- -----------------------

**6.2 BSF Substrate Protein Ceiling**

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  No combination of CFI\'s available palm streams achieves ≥15% DM CP.
  Maximum achievable \~14.5% (100% OPDC or PKE). Both strategies operate
  in the marginal CP zone (10--15%). This is accepted given low feedstock
  cost and inoculation uplift factors. N conversion factor: N × 4.67 (not
  6.25) for true protein.

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**6.3 Key Organism Categories (15 Total)**

