**8.3 VGAM Soil-Adjusted Fertiliser Value**

CFI\'s VGAM (Variable Gain Agronomic Model) adjusts fertiliser
replacement value by soil type and management tier. Four management
tiers: VGAM (Very Good Agronomic Management) / GAM / Poor / Abandoned.
Frass value is highest on Histosols (peat soils) and lowest on
Spodosols.

**8.4 Indonesian Soil Types --- Palm Estate Coverage**

  ------------- -------------- --------- ----------------------- --------------
  **Soil**      **Coverage**   **pH**    **Key Properties**      **CFI N/P
                                                                 Reduction**

  Inceptisols   39%            4.1       Best fertility; CEC     −40% N, −50% P
                                         15.4, N 2.7g/kg         

  Ultisols      24%            4.5       Clay-rich, acidic; low  Baseline
                                         BS 22% --- NPK baseline 

  Oxisols       8%             4.4       Fe/Al oxides, low P     ---
                                         retention               

  **Histosols   7%             3.8       Peat/organic; high C    **−80% N, −70%
  (peat)**                               24.5%; drainage issues  P**

  Spodosols     \~22%          4.77      Sandy, lowest           ---
                                         fertility; 31% lower    
                                         yield than Ultisols     
  ------------- -------------- --------- ----------------------- --------------

**9. Carbon Credits Module**

The carbon credits module is hardcoded using IPCC methods. All constants
are LOCKED and visible in the UI. No estimation --- FOD method for solid
residues; COD method for POME wastewater.

  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  **Parameter**           **Value**

  Method --- solid        **FOD (First Order Decay) --- IPCC 2006 Vol.5
  residues                Ch.2**

  Method --- POME         **COD (Chemical Oxygen Demand) method**

  GWP₁₀₀ (CH₄)            28

  GWP₂₀ (CH₄)             84

  MCF values              Per Verra ACM0022 v3.1

  Residue capture         EFB, OPDC, POME sludge --- default 100%;
  overrides               user-adjustable

  **CO₂e avoided (full    **\~213,827 t CO₂e/year**
  capacity)**             

  **Annual carbon         **\$4.3M -- \$6.4M/year (carbon price scenario
  revenue**               dependent)**
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  All IPCC/Verra constants are LOCKED in code. Carbon methodology
  constants cannot be overridden through the Admin Panel. Changes require
  a code update + explicit documented instruction.

