**15. Admin Panel Specification**

The Admin Panel gives CFI the ability to update reference data without
touching source code. It must be accessible only to authenticated admin
users via Supabase Auth. Seven modules are required:

  ----------------- ----------------------------- ------------------------
  **Module**        **Description**               **Supabase Table**

  **1. Chemical     Edit prices, dose rates, RSPO cfi_chemical_library
  Library Editor**  status for all 20 chemicals.  
                    PKSA \$0 is read-only ---     
                    cannot be changed via Admin   
                    Panel.                        

  **2. Biological   Add/edit organism records:    cfi_biological_library
  Library Editor**  name, category, BSF safety    
                    flag, dose rate, conflict     
                    list, notes.                  

  **3. Feedstock    Update lab values for EFB,    cfi_feedstock_values
  Value Updater**   OPDC, POME sludge. CLASS A    
                    values (guardrail-locked) are 
                    READ-ONLY --- display change  
                    history only.                 

  **4. Pricing      Update synthetic fertiliser   cfi_pricing
  Updater**         prices (Urea, TSP, MOP,       
                    Kieserite, Ag Lime, OM).      
                    Update BSF product market     
                    prices.                       

  **5.              View all guardrail-locked     cfi_guardrails
  Rule/Constraint   rules. CLASS A = READ-ONLY    
  Manager**         (code + brief + workbook      
                    update required). CLASS B/C/D 
                    = editable.                   

  **6. Lab Results  Upload new lab results        cfi_lab_results
  Importer**        (JSON/CSV). Auto-triggers     
                    delta check: if any value     
                    deviates \>20% from           
                    canonical, shows amber alert  
                    before accepting.             

  **7. Change Log   Read-only audit log. Shows    cfi_change_log
  Viewer**          every data change: timestamp, 
                    changed-by, old value, new    
                    value, class (A/B/C/D).       
  ----------------- ----------------------------- ------------------------

**15.1 Change Classification System**

  ----------- ----------------- ----------------- --------------------------
  **Class**   **Type**          **Where Updated** **Examples**

  **CLASS A** Hard constraints  Code + Brief +    OPDC yield %, OPDC press
              --- LOCKED        Workbook          MC floor, BSF gates, PKSA
                                simultaneously    \$0

  **CLASS B** Reference data    Admin Panel only  Synthetic fertiliser
                                                  prices, lab values within
                                                  ±20% of canonical

  **CLASS C** Library entries   Admin Panel only  New organisms, new
                                                  chemicals, new soil
                                                  profiles

  **CLASS D** UI/logic          Code update       New tabs, component
              adjustments                         redesigns, layout changes
  ----------- ----------------- ----------------- --------------------------

**16. Data Update Protocol**

All data updates must follow this protocol. Nothing changes without:
Classify → Log → Apply → Verify.

**16.1 General Update Workflow**

-   1\. CLASSIFY the change: Is it CLASS A, B, C, or D?

-   2\. LOG intent: Record in cfi_change_log before making any change.

-   3\. APPLY: For CLASS A --- update code + this brief + relevant
    workbook in the same session. For CLASS B/C --- Admin Panel only.

-   4\. VERIFY: Confirm the change flows correctly through all dependent
    calculations.

-   5\. CONFIRM: If delta \> 20% from canonical, amber alert must be
    shown before accepting.

**16.2 New Lab Results Workflow**

-   1\. Upload JSON/CSV via Admin Panel → Lab Results Importer.

-   2\. System auto-calculates delta vs canonical values for each
    parameter.

-   3\. If any delta \> 20%: AMBER ALERT shown --- user must explicitly
    confirm before update is accepted.

-   4\. POME Fe result auto-triggers inclusion rate recalculation (see
    Section 4.3).

-   5\. All accepted values are logged to cfi_lab_results with
    timestamp, source, and analyst name.

-   6\. CLASS A values (guardrail-locked) are shown for reference only
    --- cannot be updated via this route.

**16.3 New Chemical or Organism**

-   1\. Admin Panel → Chemical Library Editor or Biological Library
    Editor.

-   2\. All required fields must be completed before save (no partial
    records).

-   3\. For organisms: BSF safety flag is mandatory. Conflict list must
    be checked against existing organisms.

-   4\. For chemicals: RSPO status field mandatory. If RSPO = Restricted
    or Alert, a warning display flag is set automatically.

-   5\. New entries are visible immediately in the React dashboard after
    save.

**16.4 Price Changes**

-   Admin Panel → Pricing Updater.

-   Change takes effect immediately in all dashboard calculations.

-   Logged to change log with old and new values.

-   Carbon credit methodology constants are NOT editable via Admin Panel
    --- code update required.

**17. Supabase Schema**

All tables are append-only. Deletes are soft-deletes (is_active=false).
The cfi_change_log is immutable --- no row can ever be deleted from it.

**17.1 Core Tables (11 Tables)**

  ------------------------------ ----------------------------- ------------------
  **Table**                      **Purpose**                   **Key Fields**

  **cfi_guardrails**             All guardrail-locked          key, value, class,
                                 constants.                    locked
                                 is_guardrail_locked boolean.  
                                 Read-only for CLASS A.        

  **cfi_feedstock_values**       Canonical lab values for EFB, stream, parameter,
                                 OPDC, POME sludge with        value, unit,
                                 version history               source

  **cfi_chemical_library**       20 chemicals with prices,     id, name, group,
                                 dose rates, RSPO status,      rspo,
                                 safety flags                  price_usd_kg,
                                                               dose_low,
                                                               dose_high

  **cfi_biological_library**     43 organisms with BSF safety  id, name,
                                 flags, conflict lists, dose   category,
                                 rates                         bsf_safety,
                                                               conflict_ids

  **cfi_pricing**                Synthetic fertiliser and BSF  product,
                                 product market prices         price_usd, unit,
                                                               effective_date

  **cfi_lab_results**            Uploaded lab results with     stream, parameter,
                                 delta flags and approval      value, delta_pct,
                                 status                        approved_by

  **cfi_data_gaps**              Tracks confirmed data gaps    parameter, stream,
                                 (e.g. POME C:N). Prevents     status, notes
                                 estimate from being accepted  
                                 as fact.                      

  **cfi_conflict_log**           Resolved data conflicts. EE   source, parameter,
                                 29.2% pre-rejected.           reason_rejected,
                                 Immutable.                    date

  **cfi_soil_profiles**          5 Indonesian palm soil types  soil_type,
                                 with N/P reduction factors    coverage_pct, ph,
                                                               n_reduction,
                                                               p_reduction

  **cfi_change_log**             IMMUTABLE audit trail. Every  timestamp, user,
                                 data change logged here.      table, field,
                                 Never delete.                 old_value,
                                                               new_value, class

  **cfi_orchestration_agents**   7 discovery agents: status,   agent_name,
                                 schedule, last/next run       status, schedule,
                                                               last_run, next_run
  ------------------------------ ----------------------------- ------------------

