**19. Living Document Instructions**

This brief is a living document. It must be updated whenever CFI\'s
process parameters, guardrails, product targets, or dashboard
architecture change. Failure to update the brief breaks continuity
across sessions.

**19.1 When to Update This Brief**

-   Any CLASS A guardrail change (mandatory --- code + brief + workbook
    in same session)

-   Any new canonical lab value accepted or rejected

-   New organism or chemical added to libraries

-   New React dashboard version with structural changes (new tabs, new
    panels)

-   New workbook built or significantly revised

-   Any CAPEX or equipment decision confirmed (RFQs received, decisions
    made)

-   Any pricing update that changes financial model assumptions
    materially

-   New Supabase tables or schema changes

**19.2 Version Numbering**

  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------
  **Increment**           **When**

  Major (v5.0)            Complete restructure, new pipeline stages, or
                          major guardrail overhaul

  Minor (v4.3)            New sections, new CLASS A changes, or
                          significant content additions (3+ sections)

  Patch (v4.2.1)          Corrections, small additions, typo fixes, CLASS
                          B/C updates
  ----------------------- -----------------------------------------------

**19.3 How to Instruct Claude to Update This Brief**

Use this standard format when requesting a brief update:

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------
  Standard instruction: \"UPDATE BRIEF: \[describe change\]. CLASS
  \[A/B/C/D\]. \[Old value\] → \[New value\]. Update Section \[X\].\"
  Example: \"UPDATE BRIEF: OPDC moisture floor raised from 40% to 45%.
  CLASS A. Old: 40% → New: 45%. Update Sections 2, 3, 7.\"

  -----------------------------------------------------------------------

**19.4 Storage & Distribution**

-   Master copy: This Claude Project --- always upload updated .docx to
    project files

-   Working copy: /mnt/project/ directory (project files)

-   Output copy: /mnt/user-data/outputs/ (download link for each build)

-   Lovable upload: Upload current version to Lovable project knowledge
    before each build session

-   Do NOT share the brief externally without removing Section 19
    (Living Document Instructions)

